---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://ultrazoom.app/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Compare', item: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'Best Hover Zoom alternatives', item: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/hover-zoom-alternatives' },
  ],
};

const itemListSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ItemList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Ultra Zoom', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Imagus', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/imagus' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'Hover Zoom Plus', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/hover-zoom-plus' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 4, name: 'Thumbnail Zoom Plus', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/thumbnail-zoom-plus' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 5, name: 'Mage', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/mage' },
  ],
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Best Hover Zoom Alternatives in 2026 — A Privacy-First Roundup"
  description="A side-by-side ranking of every Hover Zoom alternative for Chrome, Firefox, Edge and Brave — by privacy, active maintenance, Manifest V3 support, and feature parity."
  currentPage="compare"
  og={{
    url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/hover-zoom-alternatives',
    title: 'Best Hover Zoom Alternatives in 2026',
    description: 'Every Hover Zoom alternative, ranked by privacy, maintenance, and feature parity.',
    image: 'https://ultrazoom.app/og/compare-hover-zoom-alternatives.png',
    imageWidth: 1200,
    imageHeight: 630,
  }}
  jsonLd={[breadcrumbSchema, itemListSchema]}
>
    <main class="main page-content" id="main-content">
        <h1>Best Hover Zoom alternatives in 2026</h1>

        <p class="pricing-intro">Hover Zoom was the original. Then it <a href="/blog/hover-zoom-privacy-scandal">got caught selling browsing data</a>, and the community fragmented into a dozen forks. Here&rsquo;s an honest ranking of every Hover Zoom alternative still worth installing &mdash; by privacy story, active maintenance, Manifest V3 readiness, and feature parity.</p>

        <section class="help-section" id="ranking">
            <h2>The shortlist</h2>
            <ol class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Ultra Zoom</strong> &mdash; actively maintained, MV3-native on Chrome and a current Firefox add-on, zero telemetry by design, on-device AI upscaling, video preview controls. Free core, optional Pro tier with 7-day trial. <a href="/">ultrazoom.app</a></li>
                <li><strong>Imagus</strong> &mdash; the sieve-rule classic. Massive community sieve, but development pace varies and Manifest V3 has been a struggle. <a href="/compare/imagus">Full comparison</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Hover Zoom Plus</strong> &mdash; the most-installed community fork. Useful, light on active development. <a href="/compare/hover-zoom-plus">Full comparison</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Thumbnail Zoom Plus</strong> &mdash; a Firefox classic that broke when legacy add-ons retired. Some forks remain, mostly dormant. <a href="/compare/thumbnail-zoom-plus">Full comparison</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Mage and other Hover Zoom forks</strong> &mdash; sporadic releases, single maintainer, partial MV3. <a href="/compare/mage">Full comparison</a>.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="ranking-criteria">
            <h2>How we ranked them</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Privacy story.</strong> Does the extension phone home? Is there a documented architecture? Has it ever been caught logging user data?</li>
                <li><strong>Active maintenance.</strong> Last release date, commit cadence, whether issues get answered.</li>
                <li><strong>Manifest V3 readiness.</strong> Native MV3 build, or running on borrowed time?</li>
                <li><strong>Feature parity.</strong> Hover preview, gallery navigation, theater mode, reverse image search, custom URL rules.</li>
                <li><strong>Browser coverage.</strong> Chrome, Edge, Brave, Opera, Vivaldi, Firefox.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="comparison-table">
            <h2>Side-by-side comparison</h2>
            <div class="pricing-compare-wrap">
                <table class="pricing-compare">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Feature</th>
                            <th scope="col">Ultra Zoom</th>
                            <th scope="col">Imagus</th>
                            <th scope="col">Hover Zoom Plus</th>
                            <th scope="col">Thumbnail Zoom Plus</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Active development</th>
                            <td>Every few weeks</td>
                            <td>Variable</td>
                            <td>Limited</td>
                            <td>Dormant</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Manifest V3 native</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td>Partial</td>
                            <td>Partial</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Firefox support</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td>Legacy only</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Zero telemetry guarantee</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td>Unclear</td>
                            <td>Unclear</td>
                            <td>Unclear</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Theater mode</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Reverse image search</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td>Partial</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">On-device AI upscaling</th>
                            <td>&#10003; (Pro)</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Video preview controls</th>
                            <td>&#10003; (Pro)</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="recommendation">
            <h2>Our recommendation</h2>
            <p>If you want a Hover Zoom replacement that&rsquo;s still being shipped in 2026, has a documented zero-knowledge architecture, supports current Manifest V3 on Chrome and a signed Firefox add-on, and has a real company behind the Pro tier &mdash; install Ultra Zoom. If you have a heavy custom Imagus sieve and don&rsquo;t mind the development pace, Imagus is still a credible choice; Ultra Zoom supports custom URL rules in its Pro tier for migrating sieves over.</p>
            <ul class="install-links">
                <li>
                    <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ultra-zoom/jalclpdejbeamaamcpbolkclpnleagmg" class="install-button chrome" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Install for Chrome</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/ultra-zoom/" class="install-button firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Install for Firefox</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
